{
  "name": "Generate Missing Visual Assets",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "[Implements: R32.3 / R32.4] On save of a frontend file, scan for missing image references and generate them via the kiro-gpt-bridge MCP tools. Gated on the user setting kiroGptBridge.autoGenerateAssets === true.",
  "enabled": true,
  "settingGate": {
    "setting": "kiroGptBridge.autoGenerateAssets",
    "equals": true
  },
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "**/*.tsx",
      "**/*.jsx",
      "**/*.vue",
      "**/*.svelte",
      "**/*.html",
      "**/*.css",
      "**/*.scss",
      "**/*.astro"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "[R32.3 — visual-asset hook for code edits] First, check the user setting `kiroGptBridge.autoGenerateAssets`. If it is not strictly equal to `true`, stop without taking any action. Otherwise: scan the file that was just saved for missing image references — `<img src=…>`, `<Image src=…>`, `<source src=…>`, `background-image: url(…)`, `![alt](path)`, `import x from '…image'`, and equivalent framework-specific forms. For every reference whose resolved path is inside the workspace and does not yet exist on disk, call the most appropriate kiro-gpt-bridge MCP tool from the kiro-gpt-bridge MCP server: `kiroGpt.generateLogo` / `generate_logo` for logos, `kiroGpt.generateHero` / `generate_hero` for hero images, `kiroGpt.generateIconSet` / `generate_icon_set` for icon sets, `kiroGpt.generateUiMockup` / `generate_ui_mockup` for UI mockups, otherwise `kiroGpt.generateImage` / `generate_image`. Derive each tool's `prompt` and `assetCategory`/`kind` from the surrounding code context (component name, alt text, nearby comments). Save each asset into the framework's default asset directory (auto-detected by the MCP server's path resolver). When the tool returns a `savedPath` that does not match the original missing reference, replace the reference in the source file with that exact `savedPath`. Do not emit placeholder paths or `TODO: add image` comments."
  }
}
